OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|36|  The Pap smear is a screening test for the detection of cervical cancer||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|37|  and its precursor lesions.  False positive and false negative results||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|38|  can occur. The test should be performed at regular intervals, and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|39|  positive results should be confirmed before definitive therapy.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|40|  Additional testing methods may be helpful in detecting abnormalities or||||||F

OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|75|  Interpretive criteria||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|76|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|77|  ER/PR:||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|78|  Positive:  greater than or equal to 1% of invasive tumor cells show any||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|79|  nuclear staining.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|80|  Negative:  no staining or less than 1% of invasive cells show any||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|81|  nuclear staining.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|82|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|83|  The reference ranges and cut-off to define a positive result were||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|84|  adopted from validation studies referenced below.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|85|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|86|  HER2:||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|87|  Scoring Criterion and Scoring System:||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|88|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|89|  Positive (3+) - Intense, homogeneous, dark, uniform membrane staining of||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|90|  >30% of invasive tumor cells.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|91|  Equivocal (2+) - Complete membrane staining that is either non-uniform||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|92|  or weak intensity but with obvious circumferential distribution in at||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|93|  least 10% of invasive cells, or intense complete membrane staining in||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|94|  30% or less of tumor cells.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|95|  Negative (0 or 1+) - No staining or weak incomplete membrane staining in||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|96|  any proportion of invasive tumor cells, or weak, complete membrane||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|97|  staining in less than 10% of tumor cells.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|98|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|99|  Equivocal Category for HER2 IHC results: A HER2, 2+ staining result that||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|100|  is interpreted as equivocal may not indicate gene amplification.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|101|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|102|  A FISH test for HER2 gene amplification is ordered for all HER2 IHC 2+||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|103|  results.||||||F

OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|133|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|134|  This ER/PR and HER2 immunohistochemical assay has been validated at the||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|135|  Grant/Riverside Immunohistochemistry laboratory according to the||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|136|  recently revised recommendations and guidelines from the NCCN ER/PR and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|137|  HER2 testing in Breast Cancer Task Force, and the jointly issued||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|138|  recommendations and guidelines from ASCO and the CAP.  This laboratory||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|139|  has programs in place to regularly monitor the proficiency and the||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|140|  interpretation of ER/PR and HER2 assays. The laboratory also||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|141|  participates in external quality assurance ER/PR and HER2 programs||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|142|  including the CAP proficiency testing program.||||||F

NTE|2||reflect the anticoagulation status of the patient. Therapeutic ranges
NTE|3||for INR's are: 
NTE|4||Most clinical situations:INR 2.0-3.0
NTE|5||Mechanical Prosthetic Valve:INR 2.5-3.5
NTE|6||Critical:INR >5.0

NTE|1||A D-dimer concentration of <0.5 micrograms per milliliter FEU is
NTE|2||considered a low probability for pulmonary embolus (PE) and deep venous
NTE|3||thrombosis (DVT). Results of this test should always be interpreted in
NTE|4||conjunction with the patient's medical history,clinical presentation,
NTE|5||and other findings. Clinical diagnosis should not be based on the
NTE|6||results of the D-dimer alone.

NTE|1||This individual DOES have the Methylenetetrahydrofolate
NTE|2||reductase(MTHFR) C677T gene mutation on ONE allele
NTE|3||(heterozygous mutant). Individuals heterozygous for the
NTE|4||MTHFR C677T gene mutation are at less risk for
NTE|5||hyperhomocysteinemia compared to homozygous carriers. The
NTE|6||MTHFR C677T gene mutation test does not detect other causes
NTE|7||of hyperhomocysteinemia due to acquired disorders, such as
NTE|8||deficiency of  vitamins B12, B6, or folic acid, chronic
NTE|9||renal failure, zinc  deficiency, leukemia, psoriasis, or
NTE|10||antifolate drug therapy. Consider  additional testing for
NTE|11||hemostatic disorders associated with increased thrombosis
NTE|12||risk, if indicated. Consider genetic consultation and
NTE|13||counseling of potentially affected family members regarding
NTE|14||laboratory testing.

OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|37|  The Pap smear is a screening test for the detection of cervical cancer||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|38|  and its precursor lesions.  False positive and false negative results||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|39|  can occur. The test should be performed at regular intervals, and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|40|  positive results should be confirmed before definitive therapy.||||||F

NTE|1||A PCR-based assay was utilized to test for the following
NTE|2||three mutations in the HFE gene: C282Y, H63D, and S65C.
NTE|3||Because of the minimal effect on iron metabolism associated
NTE|4||with the S65C mutation, it is only reported when it is found
NTE|5||with the C282Y mutation (i.e. if the patient has the
NTE|6||C282Y/S65C genotype).
OBX|5|TX|16182^Results|1|See Ref Lab Comment |||U|||F
NTE|1||C282Y:  Not detected.
NTE|2||H63D:   Heterozygous.  One copy of the H63D mutation
NTE|3||identified.
OBX|6|TX|16183^Interpretation|1|See Ref Lab Comment |||U|||F
NTE|1||This result suggests a low risk for either a diagnosis of or
NTE|2||predisposition for hereditary hemochromatosis (HH).
NTE|3||The diagnosis of HH cannot be excluded because approximately
NTE|4||2 to 4% of patients with HH in a North American Caucasian
NTE|5||population have this genotype. However, this genotype is
NTE|6||also found in approximately 20 to 30% of clinically normal
NTE|7||individuals.  For other ethnic or racial groups, the
NTE|8||percentage of HH patients with this genotype may differ.
NTE|9||This result does not rule out the presence of disease
NTE|10||causing mutations in other regions of the HFE gene or in
NTE|11||other genes associated with hemochromatosis.  This result
NTE|12||should be interpreted in the context of clinical
NTE|13||presentation and results of other laboratory tests (e.g.,
NTE|14||serum transferrin-iron saturation and serum ferritin).
NTE|15||The above interpretation assumes that testing is being
NTE|16||performed for a possible diagnosis of HH.  For carrier
NTE|17||testing, the interpretation of this result depends on the
NTE|18||family history and genotype of affected individuals.
NTE|19||A genetic consultation may be of benefit.
NTE|20||CAUTIONS:
NTE|21||Test results should be interpreted in context of clinical
NTE|22||findings, family history, and other laboratory data.
NTE|23||Misinterpretation of results may occur if the information
NTE|24||provided is inaccurate or incomplete.
NTE|25||Rare polymorphisms exist that could lead to false negative
NTE|26||or positive results.  If results obtained do not match the
NTE|27||clinical findings, additional testing should be considered.
NTE|28||Bone marrow transplants from allogenic donors will interfere
NTE|29||with testing. Call Mayo Medical Laboratories for
NTE|30||instructions for testing patients who have received a bone
NTE|31||marrow transplant.
NTE|32||Laboratory developed test.

NTE|2||reflect the anticoagulation status of the patient. Therapeutic ranges
NTE|3||for INR's are:

OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|101|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|102|  Positive (3+) - Intense, homogeneous, dark, uniform membrane staining of||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|103|  >30% of invasive tumor cells.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|104|  Equivocal (2+) - Complete membrane staining that is either non-uniform||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|105|  or weak intensity but with obvious circumferential distribution in at||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|106|  least 10% of invasive cells, or intense complete membrane staining in||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|107|  30% or less of tumor cells.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|108|  Negative (0 or 1+) - No staining or weak incomplete membrane staining in||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|109|  any proportion of invasive tumor cells, or weak, complete membrane||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|110|  staining in less than 10% of tumor cells.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|111|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|112|  Equivocal Category for HER2 IHC results: A HER2, 2+ staining result that||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|113|  is interpreted as equivocal may not indicate gene amplification.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|114|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|115|  A FISH test for HER2 gene amplification is ordered for all HER2 IHC 2+||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|116|  results.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|117|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|118|  Methodology||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|119|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|120|  ER/PR:||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|121|  Fixation Type and Length: Tissue was fixed in 10% neutral buffered||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|122|  formalin (Cardinal Health McGaw Park IL, Cat.C4320-105) for a minimum of||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|123|  at least 6 hours and not longer than 72 hours.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|124|  Antibody and Assay Methodology: Estrogen receptor alpha (clones 6F11)||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|125|  and Progesterone receptor (clone 312), Leica Microsystems, Newcastle||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|126|  Upon Tyne, UK).||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|127|  Control Slides Examined: In-house known ER and PR positive control||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|128|  tissue were evaluated along with the test tissue. These control slides||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|129|  run along side of this patient's sample showed appropriate staining.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|130|  Specimen Adequacy: The patient's tissue was adequate for evaluation.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|131|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|132|  HER2:||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|133|  Fixation Type and Length: Tissue was fixed in 10% neutral buffered||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|134|  formalin (Cardinal Health McGaw Park IL, Cat.C4320-105) for a minimum of||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|135|  at least 6 hours and not longer than 72 hours.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|136|  Antibody and Assay Methodology: Rabbit monoclonal anti-human HER2, clone||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|137|  4B5, (FDA-approved), (Ventana Medical Systems, Tucson, AZ).||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|138|  Control Slides Examined: External kit-slides provided by manufacturer||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|139|  (cell lines with high, low and negative HER2 protein expression), and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|140|  in-house known HER2 amplified control tissue were evaluated along with||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|141|  the test tissue. These control slides run along side of this patient's||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|142|  sample showed appropriate staining.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|143|  Specimen Adequacy: The patient's tissue was adequate for evaluation.||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|144|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|145|  ER/PR and HER2 Test Validation and Ongoing Quality Management||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|146|  ||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|147|  This ER/PR and HER2 immunohistochemical assay has been validated at the||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|148|  Grant/Riverside Immunohistochemistry laboratory according to the||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|149|  recently revised recommendations and guidelines from the NCCN ER/PR and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|150|  HER2 testing in Breast Cancer Task Force, and the jointly issued||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|151|  recommendations and guidelines from ASCO and the CAP.  This laboratory||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|152|  has programs in place to regularly monitor the proficiency and the||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|153|  interpretation of ER/PR and HER2 assays. The laboratory also||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|154|  participates in external quality assurance ER/PR and HER2 programs||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|155|  including the CAP proficiency testing program.||||||F
